{"id":"sound-8","label":"Sound","lockAfter":2,"list":[{"id":"mcq","label":"Choose the correct answer","type":"mcq","commonData":{"title":"Multiple Choice Questions"},"data":[{"questions":[{"qText":"The voice box is also called as","options":"larynx, stomach, heart, mouth"},{"qText":"Sound is a kind of ____.","options":"energy, work, force, pressure"},{"qText":"The hearing range of human ear is ____.","options":"20 Hz to 20,000 Hz\n              less than 20 Hz\n              more than 20,000 Hz\n              20 Hz to 25,000 Hz"},{"qText":"Pitch of sound is determined by its ","options":"frequency, speed, amplitude, loudness"},{"qText":"The frequency of subsonic sound is ____.","options":"less than 20 Hz\n              more than 20 Hz\n              100 Hz\n              more than 20,000 Hz"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Cochlea is a part of ___.","options":" hearing organ, sound producing organ, muscular organ, air pollution"},{"qText":"1 hertz is equal to _____.","options":"1 vibration per second\n              10 vibrations per minute\n              50 vibrations per minute\n              600 vibrations per minute"},{"qText":"Sound cannot travel through","options":" vacuum, water, air, metal"},{"qText":"The sound in the audible range is called _____ sound.","options":"sonic, ultrasonic,  subsonic visible sound"},{"qText":"Speed is _______.","options":"Distance-travelled/Time, Time/Distance-travelled, Distance-travelled × Time, Time + Distance-travelled"}]},{"allowFrac":false,"questions":[{"qText":" A pendulum oscillates 20 times in 4 seconds. Find its time period.","options":"0.2 sec, 0.5 sec, 5 sec, 4 sec"},{"qText":"Loudness of sound is determined by ___.","options":"amplitude, pitch, frequency, time period"},{"qText":"The number of vibrations made by a vibrating body in one second is ____.","options":"frequency, noise, loudness, pitch"},{"qText":"The maximum displacement of a body from its mean position is called _____.","options":"amplitude, oscillation, periodic motion, frequency"},{"qText":"The velocity of sound at 20°C is approximately","options":" 340 m/sec, 3400 m/sec, 430 m/sec, 340 km/sec"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"How sound is produced? ","options":"By vibrating bodies, By non-vibrating bodies, While applying force"},{"qText":"Vibration is also known as ____ motion.","options":"oscillatory, translatory, dynamic"},{"qText":"Frequency is expressed in ____.","options":"Hertz, Kilometer, Newton, Kelvin"},{"qText":"The number of oscillations per second is called ____ of oscillation.","options":"frequency, pitch, amplitude"}]}]}]}